00:55:51,544 --> 00:55:53,471
We're taking off with my hat out.

814
00:55:53,635 --> 00:55:55,105
Fine!

815
00:55:55,125 --> 00:55:56,595
The gas money is going on your bill anyway!

816
00:56:01,319 --> 00:56:04,234
So when do we fight Curtiss?

817
00:56:04,254 --> 00:56:07,169
No need to now.  I'm outta a job, no ones hiring bounty hunters these days!

818
00:56:07,282 --> 00:56:10,385
What about your honor?

819
00:56:10,405 --> 00:56:13,508
You can't let Curtiss run around acting like he shot you down .

820
00:56:13,624 --> 00:56:14,695
I'm a pig!

821
00:56:14,715 --> 00:56:15,786
I don't fight for honor.

822
00:56:15,806 --> 00:56:16,877
I fight for a paycheck.

823
00:56:36,602 --> 00:56:37,819
It's beautiful!

824
00:56:54,661 --> 00:56:56,254
What a fantastic hideout.

825
00:56:57,799 --> 00:56:59,469
Agh!

826
00:56:59,489 --> 00:57:01,159
It's good to stretch my legs.

827
00:57:17,945 --> 00:57:19,387
Ah!

828
00:57:19,407 --> 00:57:20,849
Looks like my hideout isn't so hidden anyway.

829
00:57:20,989 --> 00:57:22,016
Boss!

830
00:57:22,036 --> 00:57:23,063
We got the pig!

831
00:57:23,732 --> 00:57:25,826
Get off me!

832
00:57:26,011 --> 00:57:27,619
Out of the way!

833
00:57:27,961 --> 00:57:30,114
You're finished, pig.

834
00:57:30,238 --> 00:57:31,865
It's payback time.

835
00:57:31,990 --> 00:57:34,038
We've got scores to settle.

836
00:57:35,295 --> 00:57:36,702
A girl!

837
00:57:36,722 --> 00:57:38,129
We got a girl here!

838
00:57:38,223 --> 00:57:39,139
She's cute.

839
00:57:39,341 --> 00:57:40,738
So what?

840
00:57:40,758 --> 00:57:42,155
Half the world population is women.

841
00:57:42,175 --> 00:57:43,572
Idiot!

842
00:57:44,804 --> 00:57:46,959
Hey Fio is no ordinary girl!

843
00:57:46,979 --> 00:57:49,134
She's a first class seaplane engineer.

844
00:57:49,299 --> 00:57:51,134
But she's so young.

845
00:57:51,154 --> 00:57:52,989
And pretty!

846
00:57:53,214 --> 00:57:54,157
A girl engineer?

847
00:57:54,177 --> 00:57:55,120
Are you sure?

848
00:57:55,246 --> 00:57:58,169
She redesigned my plane and now it flies better than ever.

849
00:57:58,269 --> 00:58:01,189
She's young, but she's a genius!

850
00:58:01,298 --> 00:58:02,217
Wooh?

851
00:58:02,237 --> 00:58:03,156
You really mean that?

852
00:58:03,240 --> 00:58:04,892
Hey!

853
00:58:04,912 --> 00:58:06,564
I never lie about my seaplane, kid.

854
00:58:06,742 --> 00:58:08,595
Treat her with respect.

855
00:58:08,615 --> 00:58:10,468
She came along just to make sure I pay my bill.

856
00:58:11,905 --> 00:58:12,974
So you're in debt, too?

857
00:58:12,994 --> 00:58:14,063
It serves you right!

858
00:58:14,251 --> 00:58:17,697
Hey what do you say, we smash his stupid red plane to bits.

859
00:58:17,717 --> 00:58:21,163
And leave him here to rot and dead?

860
00:58:21,308 --> 00:58:22,681
Smash it?

861
00:58:22,701 --> 00:58:24,074
You destroy a work of art?

862
00:58:24,876 --> 00:58:31,092
It happens to be a one of a kind Savoy-S21   We realize it's a nice plane...

863
00:58:31,171 --> 00:58:32,108
but we have our reaons.

864
00:58:32,436 --> 00:58:33,253
Yeah?

865
00:58:33,273 --> 00:58:34,090
What are they?

866
00:58:34,196 --> 00:58:35,527
Well it's kinda complicated.

867
00:58:35,547 --> 00:58:36,878
And you call yourselves seaplane pilots?

868
00:58:37,107 --> 00:58:38,174
Step aside.

869
00:58:38,194 --> 00:58:39,261
Watch the shoes!

870
00:58:47,858 --> 00:58:53,000
My grandpa has been telling me stories of seaplane pirates ever since I was born.

871
00:58:53,200 --> 00:58:59,093
He says seaplane pirates are the most honorable and trustworthy fighters in the world!.

872
00:58:59,185 --> 00:59:04,215
Everytime they fly both the ocean and the sky purify their hearts.

873
00:59:04,366 --> 00:59:07,105
So they're braver than any pilot in the sky...

874
00:59:07,225 --> 00:59:09,329
and they are mightier than any sailor in the sea!.

875
00:59:11,266 --> 00:59:13,044
Ms.Fio!

876
00:59:13,064 --> 00:59:14,842
Thank you, you make me proud to be a seaplane pirate.

877
00:59:15,007 --> 00:59:17,861
And you should be, I can tell it's not about money or revenge.

878
00:59:17,881 --> 00:59:20,735
You are about honor!

879
00:59:22,855 --> 00:59:23,092
Yeah!

880
00:59:23,112 --> 00:59:23,349
That's right, Fio!

881
00:59:23,369 --> 00:59:23,606
Yeah To honor!

882
00:59:26,818 --> 00:59:30,486
Now that girl is something else.

883
00:59:30,608 --> 00:59:37,009
Ok Ms.Fio, we respect you so we'll not destroy the plane that you made!

884
00:59:37,100 --> 00:59:40,001
But we still hate that stinkin' pig's gut and we want payback.

885
00:59:40,100 --> 00:59:42,449
Slice that pig to bacon!

886
00:59:42,469 --> 00:59:44,818
Yeah!

887
00:59:44,952 --> 00:59:46,831
What are you morons talking about?

888
00:59:46,802 --> 00:59:48,705
You can't gangup on a fellow sea plane pilot!

889
00:59:48,725 --> 00:59:50,628
Where is your honor?

890
00:59:51,004 --> 00:59:53,678
You ought to be completely ashamed of yourselves!

891
00:59:54,132 --> 00:59:57,978
A real seaplane pirate would never fight in a pack like bunch of cowards!

892
00:59:58,345 --> 01:00:02,521
Look at Porco, he just came back so that we could have a re-match with Curtiss.

893
01:00:02,808 --> 01:00:06,358
And defend his reputation like a real sea pirate should.

894
01:00:06,645 --> 01:00:10,491
So if you wanna fight Porco honorably then you fight him in the sky!

895
01:00:12,160 --> 01:00:12,715
One on one.

896
01:00:12,735 --> 01:00:13,290
I would fight Porco...

897
01:00:13,370 --> 01:00:15,199
but my plane has engine trouble.

898
01:00:15,330 --> 01:00:16,750
You big liar!

899
01:00:16,770 --> 01:00:18,190
Quit makin' excuses.

900
01:00:18,448 --> 01:00:19,825
What should we do, Boss?

901
01:00:19,960 --> 01:00:20,816
She did make some good points.

902
01:00:20,836 --> 01:00:21,692
Yeah!

903
01:00:21,920 --> 01:00:24,216
We should pick someone who can fight Porco.

904
01:00:24,236 --> 01:00:26,532
I think we should talk to Curtiss.

905
01:00:26,675 --> 01:00:28,014
Wait a minute!

906
01:00:28,034 --> 01:00:29,373
Asking him to fight the pig again?

907
01:00:29,668 --> 01:00:31,716
Only Curtiss can beat him.

908
01:00:32,337 --> 01:00:34,010
The contract with him has already expired!

909
01:00:37,228 --> 01:00:38,114
Howdy fellas!

910
01:00:38,134 --> 01:00:39,020
What?

911
01:00:39,040 --> 01:00:39,926
It's Curtiss!

912
01:00:40,136 --> 01:00:42,436
What's he doin' here?

913
01:00:43,150 --> 01:00:45,007
I followed ya' all!

914
01:00:45,027 --> 01:00:46,884
I knew you get into trouble without me!

915
01:00:48,864 --> 01:00:50,596
Nice goin' Fio.

916
01:00:50,616 --> 01:00:52,348
Look at the mess you got me into now.

917
01:01:03,577 --> 01:01:05,079
Here..hold these.

918
01:01:09,708 --> 01:01:12,131
So do you want me to challenge for a rematch do you, pig?

919
01:01:12,512 --> 01:01:15,308
Why should I give it to ya?

920
01:01:15,328 --> 01:01:18,124
I won once already and my contract with these boys is expired.

921
01:01:18,560 --> 01:01:19,729
Well give us a proposition?

922
01:01:19,749 --> 01:01:20,918
What do you want?

923
01:01:31,688 --> 01:01:33,281
Beautiful!

924
01:01:34,399 --> 01:01:36,947
Tell you what, if I win will you marry me darlin'?

925
01:01:40,363 --> 01:01:41,615
That's what I want.

926
01:01:41,791 --> 01:01:44,195
Fine with me!

927
01:01:44,215 --> 01:01:46,619
But if Porco beats you, then you ought to pay the debt he owes me.

928
01:01:47,078 --> 01:01:48,079
Don't do it, Fio!

929
01:01:48,622 --> 01:01:50,090
Eh, backup!.

930
01:01:54,419 --> 01:01:56,968
Ms.Fio are you quite ceratin you wanna do this?

931
01:01:57,130 --> 01:01:58,803
You should ask him not me.

932
01:01:58,924 --> 01:02:00,767
These bills are kinda expensive.

933
01:02:00,884 --> 01:02:01,976
No they're not!

934
01:02:02,385 --> 01:02:03,762
Are you gonna fight or not?

935
01:02:04,679 --> 01:02:07,307
I'll gladly fight for the woman that I love!

936
01:02:07,432 --> 01:02:08,649
Good!

937
01:02:09,486 --> 01:02:11,617
Alright!

938
01:02:11,637 --> 01:02:13,768
The fight will take place first thing tomorrow morning!.

939
01:02:13,939 --> 01:02:17,489
Since Fio is doing such an honorable thing, my gang will host!

940
01:02:18,620 --> 01:02:19,340
Hey we like to host too!

941
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:20,080
Yeah!

942
01:02:20,100 --> 01:02:20,820
Yeah!

943
01:02:25,450 --> 01:02:28,169
See you later, Ms.Fio!

944
01:02:30,789 --> 01:02:31,836
This is ridiculous!

945
01:02:32,123 --> 01:02:34,842
Don't forget to show up, pig!

946
01:02:35,168 --> 01:02:38,843
Shut up, just go home already!

947
01:02:39,422 --> 01:02:40,344
Ok!

948
01:02:44,427 --> 01:02:48,978
What on Earth possessed you, to make that deal?

949
01:02:49,432 --> 01:02:53,858
Well I'm sorry, I guess I shouldn't have been ameaned.

950
01:02:54,000 --> 01:02:56,100
I'm just a stupid little girl!

951
01:03:00,026 --> 01:03:01,027
Fio?

952
01:03:01,653 --> 01:03:04,702
I should thank you for saving my life back there!

953
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:07,208
You really put yourself on the line.

954
01:03:07,836 --> 01:03:09,756
So thanks.

955
01:03:09,776 --> 01:03:11,696
It looks like we are into this thing together now.

956
01:03:12,205 --> 01:03:13,832
So you'll fight Curtiss?

957
01:03:15,844 --> 01:03:18,308
He could win you know.

958
01:03:18,328 --> 01:03:20,792
Hmm You got more honor.

959
01:03:22,309 --> 01:03:25,002
Honor?

960
01:03:25,022 --> 01:03:27,715
I hate that word, but somehow when you say it doesn't sound so bad..

961
01:03:33,403 --> 01:03:35,274
What's the matter with you?

962
01:03:35,294 --> 01:03:37,165
Are you cold?

963
01:03:37,185 --> 01:03:39,056
Fio> Oh Boy!.

964
01:03:39,868 --> 01:03:42,705
I'm shaking allover.

965
01:03:42,725 --> 01:03:45,562
My heart's pounding like crazy I guess I was really scared .

966
01:03:46,323 --> 01:03:48,872
I just didn't know you would fight for me Porco!

967
01:03:52,380 --> 01:03:52,969
Woah!

968
01:03:52,989 --> 01:03:53,578
What you doin'?

969
01:03:54,205 --> 01:03:55,252
I need a swim.

970
01:04:14,861 --> 01:04:15,803
Oh No!

971
01:04:15,823 --> 01:04:16,765
What?

972
01:04:16,936 --> 01:04:18,153
What's wrong?

973
01:04:18,897 --> 01:04:22,117
I really lew it Porco.

974
01:04:22,776 --> 01:04:24,149
I should have padded those bills!

975
01:04:24,249 --> 01:04:25,449
Curtiss would have paid a lot more!

976
01:04:28,365 --> 01:04:29,582
You're right!

977
01:05:23,753 --> 01:05:24,879
Porco?

978
01:05:25,296 --> 01:05:27,890
Can't you sleep?

979
01:05:29,342 --> 01:05:30,639
I saw...

980
01:05:32,303 --> 01:05:33,896
Maybe it was a dream.

981
01:05:35,066 --> 01:05:36,531
Go back to sleep.

982
01:05:36,551 --> 01:05:38,016
We gotta big day tomorrow.

983
01:05:39,644 --> 01:05:40,645
Porco?

984
01:05:41,197 --> 01:05:42,349
Yeah?

985
01:05:42,369 --> 01:05:43,521
Why did you turn into a pig?

986
01:05:43,950 --> 01:05:44,641
Hmm..

987
01:05:44,661 --> 01:05:45,352
All middle aged men are pigs!

988
01:05:46,953 --> 01:05:49,669
You know I've heard a lot about Capt.Marco Rossolini.

989
01:05:49,689 --> 01:05:52,405
My father was in his fighter unit.

990
01:05:53,001 --> 01:05:56,318
He told me that Marco once landed a seaplane in raging sea...  to save the life of an enemy pilot.

991
01:05:56,338 --> 01:05:59,655
I think that's amazing!

992
01:06:04,721 --> 01:06:05,702
I got it!

993
01:06:05,722 --> 01:06:06,703
What if I kiss you Porco?

994
01:06:08,548 --> 01:06:13,725
Yeah you heard the fairy tale where the girl kisses the frog and turns him back to a handsome prince?

995
01:06:14,063 --> 01:06:15,378
Cmon!

996
01:06:15,398 --> 01:06:16,713
You gotta save it for somebody special.

997
01:06:16,733 --> 01:06:18,048
For crying out loud.

998
01:06:19,893 --> 01:06:21,736
Don't you like me?

999
01:06:24,355 --> 01:06:25,732
You're a great kid.

1000
01:06:26,075 --> 01:06:28,541
You know what Fio?

1001
01:06:28,561 --> 01:06:31,027
Seeing you makes me wish I shouldn't have given up being human.

1002
01:06:31,404 --> 01:06:33,406
Now go to sleep.

1003
01:06:33,531 --> 01:06:36,125
First tell me a story, then I'll goto sleep.

1004
01:06:37,660 --> 01:06:42,583
Alright Here's a winner!

1005
01:06:51,382 --> 01:06:54,010
It was the last summer of the great war...

1006
01:06:55,303 --> 01:07:01,561
We were flying over the Adriatic, on a routine survellience patrol heading to Istria.

1007
01:07:06,648 --> 01:07:09,618
My good buddy Berlini was right beside me.

1008
01:07:10,109 --> 01:07:14,580
He had just gotten married to Gina from the Hotel Adriana.

1009
01:07:15,532 --> 01:07:18,627
And I was his best man.

1010
01:07:19,228 --> 01:07:23,419
But the war called so he had to go back to battle right after the ceremony.

1011
01:07:32,893 --> 01:07:36,318
Suddenly we were in the middle of the worst dogfight in my life.

1012
01:07:42,689 --> 01:07:46,317
Friends and enemies were falling around me like flies.

1013
01:07:46,525 --> 01:07:50,494
I had 3 planes trying to chase me down.

1014
01:07:50,646 --> 01:07:53,535
And all I thought about was myself.

1015
01:07:53,555 --> 01:07:56,444
Soon I realised I was the only one left from my unit.

1016
01:07:56,749 --> 01:07:59,170
But the enemy never let up.

1017
01:07:59,190 --> 01:08:01,611
I feel my guts out trying to get away.

1018
01:08:01,963 --> 01:08:04,654
My hands and feet went numb.

1019
01:08:04,674 --> 01:08:07,365
I could feel myself starting to blackout.

1020
01:08:07,485 --> 01:08:11,846
I was sure I was gonna die then suddenly everything around me turned white.

1021
01:08:12,130 --> 01:08:13,131
White?

1022
01:08:13,256 --> 01:08:16,055
Yeah, it was the strangest thing I ever seen.

1023
01:08:17,244 --> 01:08:21,000
A light that was so pure, I figured I must be in heaven.

1024
01:08:21,129 --> 01:08:23,162
Then I realized that I had flown into a cloud.

1025
01:08:23,182 --> 01:08:25,215
I was so exhausted that...

1026
01:08:25,325 --> 01:08:27,525
I couldn't hold the stick to fly my plane.

1027
01:08:27,812 --> 01:08:31,066
But the plane just kept on flying.

1028
01:08:57,258 --> 01:08:58,931
Flew by itself?

1029
01:08:59,395 --> 01:09:02,214
Yeah it was perfectly quiet.

1030
01:09:02,234 --> 01:09:05,053
And the sky was beautiful...

1031
01:09:05,558 --> 01:09:10,564
then I saw this strange white band high above me.

1032
01:09:38,132 --> 01:09:40,430
Berlini, I thought you were dead!

1033
01:09:44,107 --> 01:09:45,259
Come back here!

1034
01:09:45,279 --> 01:09:46,431
Where do you think you are going?

1035
01:09:59,455 --> 01:10:01,187
What about Gina?

1036
01:10:01,207 --> 01:10:02,939
You can't leave her alone.

1037
01:10:03,092 --> 01:10:03,843
Let me go instead!

1038
01:10:03,863 --> 01:10:04,614
Hold on!

1039
01:10:45,158 --> 01:10:50,164
When I came to, I was skimming just above the sea, all alone.

1040
01:10:53,541 --> 01:10:56,169
God was telling you, it wasn't your time yet.

1041
01:10:58,214 --> 01:11:00,597
You think?

1042
01:11:00,617 --> 01:11:03,000
Seems to me, he was telling me maybe I was a pig and I deserved to be all alone.

1043
01:11:03,311 --> 01:11:04,565
You can't believe that!

1044
01:11:04,585 --> 01:11:05,839
You're a good person!

1045
01:11:06,381 --> 01:11:08,078
No!

1046
01:11:08,098 --> 01:11:09,795
The good ones are the ones who died.

1047
01:11:09,815 --> 01:11:11,512
Or maybe I'm dead, life as a pig.

1048
01:11:12,111 --> 01:11:13,553
It's the same thing as hell.

1049
01:11:13,573 --> 01:11:15,015
Now go to sleep.

1050
01:11:17,523 --> 01:11:20,117
That stupid kid, he sold me rusted cartridges.

1051
01:11:22,497 --> 01:11:25,003
I think you are a great human being, Porco.

1052
01:11:25,023 --> 01:11:27,529
I'm glad you're still around.

1053
01:11:28,534 --> 01:11:29,581
Good night!

1054
01:11:54,227 --> 01:11:57,071
Place your bets here!

1055
01:11:58,699 --> 01:12:00,289
Box seats here!

1056
01:12:00,309 --> 01:12:01,899
Place your wager!

1057
01:12:12,171 --> 01:12:14,612
Buncha morons!

1058
01:12:14,632 --> 01:12:17,073
They'll turn this into a big party Are all of these people air pirates?

1059
01:12:17,260 --> 01:12:19,578
No they are trash all over the Mediterranean.

1060
01:12:19,598 --> 01:12:21,916
Gangsters, smugglers, gamblers...

1061
01:12:22,213 --> 01:12:25,592
Yeah you might have a handful of few respectful people but I doubt it.

1062
01:12:26,736 --> 01:12:28,256
Wow!

1063
01:12:28,276 --> 01:12:29,796
Not only will I get a wife but also will be getting more famous!

1064
01:12:30,398 --> 01:12:31,988
Ten minutes to start!

1065
01:12:32,008 --> 01:12:33,598
Ten minutes to start!

1066
01:12:34,277 --> 01:12:36,931
Listen up!

1067
01:12:36,951 --> 01:12:39,605
This is a final bouter between Porco Rosso and Donald Curtiss.

1068
01:12:40,147 --> 01:12:46,120
So if one of you fights dirty, you'll be disrespected by seaplane pilots for eternity !

1069
01:12:46,414 --> 01:12:48,255
Cmon!

1070
01:12:48,275 --> 01:12:50,116
No speeches, no speeches!

1071
01:12:53,588 --> 01:12:55,508
Quite down !

1072
01:12:55,528 --> 01:12:57,448
The next person I hear whining is dead meat!

1073
01:13:06,726 --> 01:13:07,855
Why not drop a bomb?

1074
01:13:07,875 --> 01:13:09,004
Really gets them quite.

1075
01:13:09,427 --> 01:13:13,278
This fight will decides the fate of Ms.Fio...

1076
01:13:14,378 --> 01:13:14,685
who you all love and respect!

1077
01:13:14,705 --> 01:13:15,012
So keep your mouth shut.

1078
01:13:16,569 --> 01:13:18,660
You got that?

